==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tillage
<hw>Till"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
operation, practice, or art of tilling or preparing land for seed, and
keeping the ground in a proper state for the growth of crops.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place tilled or cultivated; cultivated
land.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Cultivation; culture; husbandry; farming;
agriculture.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tillandsia</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
